\\\\
&=\displaystyle\lim_{x\to 0}\dfrac{\dfrac{d}{dx}[e^x-1]}{\dfrac{d}{dx}[2x]}\qquad\gray{\text{L’Hôpital’s rule}}
\\\\
&=\displaystyle\lim_{x\to 0}\dfrac{e^x}{2}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{e^{(0)}}{2}\qquad\gray{\text{Substitution}}
\\\\
&=\dfrac12
\end{align}$

Note that we were only able to use L’Hôpital’s rule because the limit $\displaystyle\lim_{x\to 0}\dfrac{\dfrac{d}{dx}[e^x-1]}{\dfrac{d}{dx}[2x]}$ actually exists.

